 color=#333399>(6/6/01 3:06:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> I am a 6th lvl Woodelf Druid, I have only been playing for a few days now.  I have researched many EQ sites to get alot of information.  My question is on snare for kiting.  I have been attempting kiting, but truthfully snare seems to basically suck.  Either that or every monster has the spell/skill of Warp factor 9.   How does kiting work when they run so d**n fast.  You would be running to kingdom come before you finished it off.  I was initially under the impression that they would be in slow motion and you only had to take a few steps to keep away from it.  Plus all of them where all up in my butt before the spell even finished.  Is this a system used at higher than my lvl?  Snare get stronger with each lvl?  Am I just doing something wrong?  Thanks in advance for all advice and help.<br>
<br>
Ayano <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uyanguboris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>YanguBoris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 3:10:21 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> Kiting takes forever without sow. When you can slow them down AND speed yourself up, then it becomes worth it. <p><font face="Tahoma">46 Wood Elf Druid, Vazaelle<br>20 Ogre Warrior, Vazaelle<p><i>"We are all born mad. Some remain so."</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubremen7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bremen7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 3:36:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Snare</span><hr size=1> Snare is quite literally the best spell in the game. But it won't do you a lot of good with regard to kiting until, as the above poster said, you can get SoW at level 14. <br>
Then it rocks and will be your best friend.<br>
<br>
For now I would stick to melee-ing (at least in part) in order that your defense skill continues to rise concomitant with your level. When you get higher up Defense is crucial and if you wait too long you'll be in trouble or at pains to make it rise. <br>
<br>
Don't worry about kiting just yet. Learn how to group and do the things you should be doing at your level.<br>
<br>
Peace.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uyanguboris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>YanguBoris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 3:52:21 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> Aye, your best bet for destroying this creatures is snaring, run, nuke, run, nuke, thorn yourself, and melee. Throw some nukes in during the fight if it looks like your health is dropping too fast =) <p><font face="Tahoma">46 Wood Elf Druid, Vazaelle<br>20 Ogre Warrior, Vazaelle<p><i>"We are all born mad. Some remain so."</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unanaja.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nanaja</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/star2.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 4:14:30 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/purplesprite.gif WIDTH=82 HEIGHT=90></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> When you get SoW at 14th your life will be blissful. Unfortunately, basic snare doesn't last long. :( (You get Ensnare at 29 which lasts 5 minutes and is MUCH better.) The theory on kiting is you SoW yourself, and snare the mob so you're running significantly faster than the mob. So until you get SoW, if you wish to kill mobs with spells, snare them, root and nuke. Otherwise, thorn yourself and tank it out while meleeing.<br>
<br>
Good luck!. :)  <p><CENTER>
<A HREF="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/Profiles/NanajaProfile.html"><IMG SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/EQimages/NanajaSpriteSig.jpg" BORDER=0 ALT="Click to see character stats."></A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usavenmistwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saven MistWolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 7:07:02 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.homestead.com/wolf29/files/wolfwalk.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> Actually I believe ensnare lasts ~11 minutes. <p><B><I>Saven MistWolf</B></I><BR>
<B><I> Druid of the 55th Season</B></I><BR><B><I>Wild Knights, The Rathe</B></I><BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unanaja.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nanaja</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/star2.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 7:15:06 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/purplesprite.gif WIDTH=82 HEIGHT=90></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> Never really timed how long ensnare lasts...all I know is that it lasts too damn long when I accidentially snare myself. =/ <p><CENTER>
<A HREF="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/Profiles/NanajaProfile.html"><IMG SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/EQimages/NanajaSpriteSig.jpg" BORDER=0 ALT="Click to see character stats."></A></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufforestwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fforestwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 7:32:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What's with snare?</span><hr size=1> The comment above about not using snare and kiting without Spirit of Wolf (SoW) is spot-on.  If you try to kite without SoW, the mob will be on your butt hammering, which is something that is good to know about snare (and after level 29, ensnare): this spell REALLY aggro's mobs - they do not like being snared.  As mentioned in the earlier posts, melee a little or let your group-mates pound on the mob while you meditate or nuke or melee with 'em, at this level you can melee, but that will gradually slow down as your melee skill limits kick in (Warriors and other fighters' melee skills go up at (5 x level) +5, while ours' and other clerics only go up at (level x 4) + 4.)<br>
<br>
Also, as mentioned in some earlier posts, snare builds length with level, eventually maxing out at about 2 minutes' duration, while the level 29 Ensnare lasts 10 minutes at first, and I believe goes to a max of about 12 minutes as level goes up.  It also is a great aggro spell, if you want a mob on you.  For  example, you're at the large orc camp in East commons and you group's wizard nuked a centurion, which immediately ran to him and started pounding him/her into beetle paste.  If you haven't already snared the orc, do it immediately and see how fast he'll come visit you (Second bit of wisdom buried in this example, of course, is snare first, so they can't run.  This will serve you well in dungeons later in druid life, when you're in Sol A or either level of Guk, where mobs will run when low on life, and if your group doesn't stop them, return with 55 of their friends.  &lt;humor warning&gt;  This is why druids get evac spells, so we can live if we're quick-thinking after we miss that critical snare.).  Good luck, brother druid, be well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvirale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Virale</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 10:35:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> Snare Duration: Caps at 3 minutes, but I think it's 20 or 30 seconds per level (at level 1 it royally sucks for duration)<br>
<br>
ENSnare Duration: ~20 or 30 minutes, thisd one almost never runs out on me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaliciaswiftfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salicia Swiftfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 3:23:24 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/FEBertoxx/SALSTAMP.JPG HEIGHT=200 WIDTH=100 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> <I>ENSnare Duration: ~20 or 30 minutes, thisd one almost never runs out on me. </I><br>
<br>
Nope, only about 10 to 11 minutes, I've had ensnare wear off on long quads before (which sucks IMO, hard to round them all up again) Granted that hasn't happened to me for about 8 levels now... <p><p><a href="http://www.eqdivine.net"><img src="http://members.theglobe.com/FEBertoxx/SIGPIC54.JPG" width="312" height="122"></a></p>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eridon>Eridon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 4:26:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Snare/ensare are great except for Resists</span><hr size=1> No doubt that snare/ensnare are wonderful spells but do agro and resist alot.  I'm currently in OT and find it's typical to get 3 or 4 resists while attepmting to snare anything from blue to yellow cons, reds can easily take 5 attempts.  Just last night I was trying to ensnare a blue Rino (boy are they fast) and got 3 resists in a row, it's a bummer when ya gotta zone for a blue.<br>
<br>
As a side note, it seems that resists/fizzles always come in clumps.  I'll have periods where I hardly get either and then other periods where I sware I could'nt snare a bat in misty.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubuzwat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Buzwat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 6:16:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Snare pre SoW</span><hr size=1> The main thing that snare does at your lvl or any lvl pre 14 is it will stop the mob from running once it get to about 25% and will just stand there and let you beat on it with your pointy little stick.  I hate to run and hated it when the mob would take off running as its health dropped.  Snared it and then I could enjoy a pipe wack it everyonce in a while and volla dead mob.  <br>
<br>
Cheers<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucuchulainekynthelig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cuchulaine Kynthelig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 6:34:10 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> Actually, kiting kind of sucks at 14-18 too, unless you go to lavastorm. Ignite is worthless for kiting. When you hit 19, you have SoW, snare, and a decent DD spell (Careless lightning). That's when a druid's kiting career really starts. <br>
<br>
Doing it before then is a waste of time. Just get to level 9, and then porcupine your way to 19. Here is the way I suggest:<br>
<br>
1-8: however you can. you are almost as effective as a melee in these levels. <br>
<br>
9-18: porcupine. melee with thorns up. keep them snared incase you have to bail, and a DOT on them helps, too. <br>
<br>
19-33: DD-kite. <br>
<br>
34-48: quad-kite<br>
<br>
49-60: quad-kite when you can, root-DoT when you can't. <br>
<br>
Alternatiely, you could group the entire time. It will take longer, but it's a heck of a lot more fun ;) I pretty much gouped through all my levels, but did some soloing. <br>
