"Have you hugged your druid today?"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unuvanaeagetalon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nuvana Eagetalon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 7:08:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> thats because snare is over all useless at your lvl unfortunetly. It's to slow, and to effectivly kite, you need sow ).....However, it kicks much @$$ at higher lvls :)<br>
<br>
Nuvana<br>
55 druid <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulilwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LilWolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 8:05:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> Lets actually answer the what I think he wants to know.<br>
<br>
at level 6... you are a tank!  You will stay a tank until 16th or so (or at least have the ability to tank an enemy down).<br>
<br>
At your level, You can get some spells between hits from the mobs.  So stand in, wack away, and cast a few times.  It also helps to pull with harmony (for camps) and flamelick (to pull with lower ac and do a few points of damage).<br>
<br>
At level 9, you can start porcupining... Thats fun.  At that point, you will want to do this.  buff self. med. then firefist, med, shield of thorns, med a tic or to.  pull.  Some people don't use the firefist, but it always seemed to help for me.<br>
<br>
good luck<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueloriar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EloriaR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 8:11:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> Ditto all the comments.  kiting requires you to get far enough ahead of the mob to be able to stop, cast a DD and perhaps sit and med for a couple of ticks or more. Until you have SoW, you cant get far enough ahead even with snared mobs to do this. <br>
<br>
What is effective, if you are not already doing so, is to keep you skin like wood buf up all the time, then start a fight with snare to get their attention and cast flame lick as it moves towards you. This is a minor DoT, and the only one you have till lvl 14 and stinging swarm, it also debufs a few ac from the mob as well.  With this tactic my now retired lvl 8 druid was tanking evens by throwing in a DD or two, and even tanking two blues at once.<br>
<br>
Eloria Rivermist lvl 32 Druid<br>
Ekatrina lvl 8 Druid (retired)<br>
Tomaso lvl 11 Cleric <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquazare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quazare</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 8:59:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What's wth snare?</span><hr size=1> Has anyone noticed Ensnare causing a majot taunt?? As of late, As soon as I ensare, the mob charges right for me, even with 3 tanks on it.. <p><img src="http://members.home.net/radink/images/qsig.jpg">
<BR>
